"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443077","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-13","<p>The Ministerial Working Group for Maritime Growth met for the first time on 30 November 2015. The government departments which attended that meeting were the Department for Transport, the Department for Business, Innovation &amp; Skills, the Ministry of Defence, the Department for the Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs, Her Majesty’s Treasury and the Department for Culture, Media &amp; Sport. Those Government departments with interests in future cross cutting discussions will be invited to further meetings.</p><br /><p>The current expectation is that this group will meet twice in 2016 with a review at the end of the year to determine future needs.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-13T15:00:44.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443077/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443077/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Maritime Growth Ministerial Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which departments have members on the cross-departmental Maritime Business Services working group; and how often he expects that group to meet.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","21242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443078","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-12","<p>A range of communications activities are used to inform members of the public about road works taking place on major A roads and motorways, including information issued to the media and updates to pages on the Highways England and Traffic England web pages.</p><br /><p>In addition to this, letters are issued to organisations, businesses and communities affected directly by the works. Highways England will also undertake specific community and business-to-business meetings for larger scale closures within the local area of each project if required.</p><br /><p>As a standard, information and updates are issued a minimum of seven days in advance wherever possible.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-12T14:21:20.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443078/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443078/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Roads: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what mechanisms are in place to ensure that the public are made fully aware beforehand of planned road works to be carried out by contractors on trunk roads and motorways which involve either lane or whole carriageway closures.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","21409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443079","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Passenger usage at Stratford International station in 2012 was 0.96m. In 2013, usage was 0.87m. In 2014, usage was 1.02m. In 2015, usage was 1.36m. The Office of Rail and Road publishes annual figures on station usage, which are available on their website<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup>.</p><br /><p><sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup>http://orr.gov.uk/statistics/published-stats/station-usage-estimates</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-11T16:14:34.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443079/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443079/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Stratford Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many passengers have used Stratford International station in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443080","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Ministers and officials regularly discuss policy options with Her Majesty’s Treasury and colleagues in other government departments.</p><br /><p>I refer the honourable Member to my answer to the honourable Member for Alyn and Deeside (Mark Tami), on 2 November 2015 on the subject of sustainable aviation fuels and representations received as part of the work of the Transport Energy Task Force <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-23/13225/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-23/13225/</a>. I have also met with representatives from industry to discuss the potential of sustainable low carbon fuels in aviation.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","21334","2016-01-11T14:22:04.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443080/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443080/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with (a) HM Treasury and (b) other government departments on the extension of renewable transport fuels obligation beyond road transport.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","21321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443081","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-14","<p>The Government does not issue guidance to the private parking industry on the levels of penalties for motorists. The private parking sector currently operates on a model of self-regulation, and parking companies predominantly obtain access to DVLA data by being a member of one of the two Accredited Trade Associations. These Trade Associations set out in their codes of practice that the maximum level should be no more than £100. Both Trade Associations suggest their members offer a reduced rate of at least 40% if payment is made within 14 days of the issue of the charge notice.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-01-14T17:16:43.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443081/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443081/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-06","Parking Offences: Fines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department issues to the private parking industry on the appropriate levels of penalties for motorists.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","21345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443082","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Network Rail has informed me that problems with signalling equipment caused delays to some Southeastern services via London Bridge on 4, 5 and 6 of January. On the morning of 4th January, a track circuit failed near Cannon Street. On the evening of 5th January a track circuit failed on the line to Charing Cross and Network Rail was not able to rectify the fault until the morning of the 6th.</p><br /><p>Network Rail and Southeastern worked together to ensure the issues were rectified as quickly as possible and passenger disruption was minimised.</p><br /><p>I remain committed to ensuring disruption is kept to a minimum while we continue the vital Thameslink Programme works to improve capacity and reliability through one of the busiest rail routes in Europe.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-11T14:36:34.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443082/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443082/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","London Bridge Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will request that Southeastern Trains and Network Rail explain the reasons for disruption to services at London Bridge on 4, 5 and 6 January 2016; and if he will publish the responses of those organisations to that request.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","21328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443083","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-11","<p>Ministers and officials regularly discuss policy options with Her Majesty’s Treasury and colleagues in other government departments.</p><br /><p>I refer the honourable Member to my answer to the honourable Member for Alyn and Deeside (Mark Tami), on 2 November 2015 on the subject of sustainable aviation fuels and representations received as part of the work of the Transport Energy Task Force <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-23/13225/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-10-23/13225/</a>. I have also met with representatives from industry to discuss the potential of sustainable low carbon fuels in aviation.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","21321","2016-01-11T14:22:04.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443083/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443083/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Aviation: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what representations the Government has received from the aviation and aerospace industries on supporting investment in development of cleaner jet fuels.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","21334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443084","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-15","<p>The Cycle to Work Scheme is an employee benefit covered by an exemption and therefore employers do not have to make an annual tax return regarding the benefit.</p><br /><p>The Cycle to Work Alliance (made up of Cyclescheme, Cycle Solutions, Evans Cycles and Halfords) have provided figures of the take up from Jan –September 2015 141,454 people participated in the scheme.</p><br /><p>A recent survey by the Alliance showed that 62% of participants in the scheme were either non-cyclists, novice cyclists (cycling less than once a month) or occasional cyclists (cycling once or twice a month) before joining the scheme. Having joined the scheme 79% of respondents described themselves as enthusiastic cyclists.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","21194","2016-01-15T11:53:37.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443084/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443084/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of the cycle to work scheme on the number of non-cyclists taking up cycling.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","21193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443085","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-15","<p>The Cycle to Work Scheme is an employee benefit covered by an exemption and therefore employers do not have to make an annual tax return regarding the benefit.</p><br /><p>The Cycle to Work Alliance (made up of Cyclescheme, Cycle Solutions, Evans Cycles and Halfords) have provided figures of the take up from Jan –September 2015 141,454 people participated in the scheme.</p><br /><p>A recent survey by the Alliance showed that 62% of participants in the scheme were either non-cyclists, novice cyclists (cycling less than once a month) or occasional cyclists (cycling once or twice a month) before joining the scheme. Having joined the scheme 79% of respondents described themselves as enthusiastic cyclists.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","21193","2016-01-15T11:53:37.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443085/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443085/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the contribution of the cycle to work scheme to meeting the Government's objective to double the number of journeys made by bicycle by 2020.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","21194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443086","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-15","<p><strong></strong></p><p>The changes to the administration of vehicle excise duty are expected to save the public purse £13.8m per year. These savings are made up of the elements shown in the table below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>No longer having to print or store tax discs.</p></td><td><p>£1.3m pa</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>No longer having to post tax discs to customers.</p></td><td><p>£7.9m pa</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>No longer having to process applications for vehicle excise duty refunds (which are now paid automatically without the need for an application) or handle enquiries about lost or missing tax discs.</p></td><td><p>£1.2m pa</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Reduction in Post Office Ltd costs as they no longer issue paper tax discs, but offer an assisted digital service instead.</p></td><td><p>£3.4m pa</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Business will also save an estimated £8.6m per year from the changes. The savings arise from leasing companies no longer having to post tax discs to customers or businesses having to apply for refunds of vehicle excise duty and paying to replace lost or stolen tax discs.</p><br /><p>There are also one-off costs of £5.7m made up of the elements shown in the table below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DVLA IT and systems changes/updates,</p></td><td><p>£4m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Familiarisation costs to the General Public and Business in understanding the changes</p></td><td><p>£1.7m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /> <br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-15T11:34:39.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443086/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443086/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the costs and benefits of ending the paper vehicle tax disc.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","21347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443087","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-15","<p>Requests to the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency for vehicle keeper data can be made electronically or manually by post.</p><br /><p>In 2015, 3,623,724 requests for vehicle keeper data from private parking companies were made electronically. A further 253,500 requests were made manually by post. The figure for manual requests includes enquiries from private parking companies and other organisations or individuals who can demonstrate reasonable cause for needing the information.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-15T11:40:17.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443087/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443087/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Parking Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many requests have been made to the DVLA for vehicle owner addresses in the last 12 months by private parking companies.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","21351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443088","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-15","<p>The Department is working with other parts of Government to encourage and enable more people to become lorry drivers, including via apprenticeships and action related to Jobcentre Plus.</p><br /><p>The Department is taking steps to ensure that the increased demand for driving tests is accommodated through recruiting driving examiners and providing increased numbers of test appointments.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-15T11:48:55.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443088/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443088/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-06","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of new HGV drivers who will be required in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","21357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443089","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-11","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","21413 ; 21414 ; 21415","2016-01-11T13:52:08.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443089/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443089/answer","Combined 21412, 21413, 21414, 21415 FINAL.pdf","Combined 21412, 21413, 21414, 21415 FINAL.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Employment / Unemployment","UKSA Letter to Member - Employment / Unemployment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443089/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-06","Unemployment: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people have been unemployed in (a) Jarrow constituency, (b) South Tyneside and (c) the North East in each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","21412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443090","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>We do not have the information requested at this level.</p><br /><p>I can confirm that in February 2012, 375,000 letters explaining the State Pension age changes were sent to men and women (across Great Britain and Overseas) with a date of birth in the range 06/10/1954 to 05/04/1955.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-11T16:28:41.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443090/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443090/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","State Retirement Pensions: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many women in Preston constituency who were born in November 1954 have been notified of changes in the age at which they will receive the state pension; and when his Department notified each such person.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","21183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443091","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>Men or women who reach State Pension age on or after 6 April 2016 will be eligible to receive the new State Pension and will do so as long as they have at least 10 qualifying years. Estimates of the number of pensioners in Great Britain who do not have 10 qualifying years will shortly be published in ‘Impact of New State Pension (nSP) on an Individual’s Pension Entitlement – Longer Term Effects of nSP’.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-11T14:52:16.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443091/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443091/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","State Retirement Pensions: Eligibility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) men and (b) women will not qualify for a pension under the new state pension rules.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","21180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443092","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>The Department has no plans to collect this data.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-12T14:43:44.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443092/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443092/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Employment and Support Allowance: Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will make it its policy to collect data on the cause of death of individuals who have flowed off incapacity benefit or severe disablement allowance and employment and support allowance whose date of death was at the same time; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","21224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443093","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>The Government is fighting hard to fix the aspects of our EU membership that cause so much frustration in Britain - so we get a better deal for Britain and secure our future. The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-12T12:57:20.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443093/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443093/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Department for Work and Pensions: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to prepare for the outcome of the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","21259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443094","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>The data is not available in financial years (April-March) only in academic years (August-July). I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 5 January 2016 to her previous question 20685</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-12T13:02:48.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443094/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443094/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Social Security Benefits: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 15 December 2015 to Question 19711, if he will provide equivalent data for the financial years 2010-11, 2011-12 and 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","21215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443095","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>Work began in May 2014 following publication of the Industrial Injuries Advisory Committee’s report on Dupuytren’s Contracture. It is expected that a decision whether or not to add it to the list of prescribed diseases will be made early this year and will take account of the potential costs involved and other relevant factors.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","21220 ; 21241","2016-01-12T14:19:14.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443095/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443095/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit: Dupuytren's Contracture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when work first began in his Department on consideration of the proposal to include Dupuytren's contracture in the list of industrial injuries recognised for disablement benefits.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","21219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443096","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>Work began in May 2014 following publication of the Industrial Injuries Advisory Committee’s report on Dupuytren’s Contracture. It is expected that a decision whether or not to add it to the list of prescribed diseases will be made early this year and will take account of the potential costs involved and other relevant factors.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","21219 ; 21241","2016-01-12T14:19:14.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443096/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443096/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit: Dupuytren's Contracture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answers of 8 December 2015 to Question 18144 and 22 December 2015 to Question 19937 on Dupuytren's contracture, what his Department's timetable is for considering whether to add that condition to the list of industrial injuries disablement benefit discussions.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","21220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443097","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>The technology for Universal Credit delivery and rollout has been developed in such a way as to support the needs of the numbers and types of people who access Universal Credit at any given time. We do not have a detailed point-in-time breakdown for the dates given.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-11T17:46:08.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443097/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443097/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of the new technology required to implement universal credit was completed by 1 January in (a) 2012, (b) 2013, (c) 2014, (d) 2015 and (e) 2016.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443098","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p>However, the latest statistics indicate that the majority of existing Universal Credit claimants will see no change in entitlement as a result of the April 2016 changes. This is either because they are not yet in work or because they are already in work with earnings above the relevant threshold.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-11T17:46:24.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443098/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443098/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of claimants of universal credit who will be affected by the changes to benefits taking effect from April 2016.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443099","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>The vast majority of existing Universal Credit claimants will see no change in entitlement. Those who are in work and who are affected will receive additional support from their work coach and, where appropriate, from the locally administered flexible support fund.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-11T16:25:35.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443099/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443099/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the average change in entitlement for existing universal credit claimants who are in work as a result of changes to benefits taking effect in April 2016.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","21337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443100","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-14","<p>The latest available information on Jobseeker’s Allowance sanctions, including the number of Mandatory Reconsiderations and Appeals, is published at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a>:</p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><br /><p>Please note Mandatory reconsiderations were introduced in 28th October 2013.</p><br /><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development. Northern Ireland statistics can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-14T12:25:15.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443100/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443100/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Jobseeker's Allowance: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants of jobseeker's allowance in (a) Jarrow constituency, (b) South Tyneside, (c) the North East and (d) the UK who have disputed the sanction of their benefit have had that sanction overturned after reconsideration in each of the past five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","21369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443101","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-12","<p>Work began in May 2014 following publication of the Industrial Injuries Advisory Committee’s report on Dupuytren’s Contracture. It is expected that a decision whether or not to add it to the list of prescribed diseases will be made early this year and will take account of the potential costs involved and other relevant factors.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","21219 ; 21220","2016-01-12T14:19:14.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443101/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443101/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit: Dupuytren's Contracture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential cost of including Dupuytren's Contracture in the list of Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit diseases.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","21241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443102","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>As at 30<sup>th</sup>November 2015 the gender figures are:</p><br /><p>Female 57,907 (68.5%)</p><p>Male 26,568 (31.5%)</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-11T12:32:01.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443102/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443102/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Department for Work and Pensions: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people of each gender work in his Department.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","21284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443103","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-11","<p>A transcript of the debate was passed to the Danish authorities, via the Danish Deputy Chief Prosecutor, on 27 November 2015.</p><p>The Danish authorities have since confirmed that their State Attorney is reviewing the case, and is expected to make a decision on whether to re-open the case or agree that the original findings were correct, in January 2016.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-11T14:50:46.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443103/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443103/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Stephen O'Malley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what representations he has made to the Danish government on the death of Stephen O'Malley since the adjournment debate of 25 November 2015.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","21380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443104","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-14","<p>The latest available information on Jobseeker’s Allowance sanctions, including the number of Mandatory Reconsiderations and Appeals, is published at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a>:</p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><br /><p>Please note Mandatory reconsiderations were introduced in 28th October 2013.</p><br /><p>Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development. Northern Ireland statistics can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-14T12:06:31.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443104/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443104/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-06","Jobseeker's Allowance: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants of jobseeker's allowance in (a) Jarrow constituency, (b) South Tyneside, (c) the North East and (d) the UK have received a sanction of their benefit in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","21297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443262","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>I refer the hon. member to my answer of 23 November 2015 (PQ No 16855).</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-01-12T17:19:13.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443262/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443262/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Kashmir","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions were held during the recent visit to the UK by the Indian Prime Minister on Kashmir.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","902982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443265","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>The Government is negotiating reform of the EU and a new relationship for Britain with the EU to fix the aspects of our membership that cause so much frustration in Britain. Following a substantive and constructive discussion at the December European Council, Member States agreed to work toward ‘mutually satisfactory solutions’ at the February European Council.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-12T17:21:55.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443265/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443265/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had in the Council of the EU as part of negotiations on the UK's membership of the EU on free movement of people in the EU and access to in-work benefits.","false","Biography information for Pat Glass","North West Durham","Pat Glass","902980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443902","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>I refer the hon. Gentleman to my statement of 5 January on Saudi Arabia, Official Report, column 93. The British Government is concerned about the executions of 47 people over the New Year. We have raised our concerns with the Saudi authorities. I did so most recently on 4 January. We use the strength of our relationship to encourage reform.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-12T16:44:58.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443902/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/443902/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Saudi Arabia: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights situation in Saudi Arabia.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","902985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444007","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-15","<p>I have discussed Syria with Foreign Minister Lavrov at meetings of the International Syria Support Group, most recently on 18 December in New York. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), discussed Syria with President Putin at the G20 Summit in Antalya, and in a telephone conversation on 9 December following Parliament’s vote to support military action against Daesh in Syria.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-15T13:59:18.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444007/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444007/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation on the situation in Syria.","false","Biography information for David Rutley","Macclesfield","David Rutley","902974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444008","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>We welcome the signature of the Libyan Political Agreement on 17 December which paves the way for a new Government of National Accord in Libya. The security situation remains fragile and it is vital that the new government is formed quickly to tackle the threats from Daesh and people smuggling.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-12T16:30:14.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444008/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444008/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Libya: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the political situation in Libya.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","902978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444009","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>It is no secret that we have long hoped for a more mature bilateral relationship with whomever succeeded the Kirchner administration.</p><p>There are undoubted economic benefits for both of our countries, if President Macri can help Argentina to overcome years of mismanagement.</p><p>But let me assure this House that our position on the Falklands will not change.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-01-12T15:56:36.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444009/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444009/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444009/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Argentina: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for the UK's relations with Argentina of the presidential election in that country in November 2015.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","902981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444010","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>We remain concerned that a number of Chinese lawyers and activists detained since July have not been released.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymeade and Weybridge, (Mr Hammond), raised this issue with the Chinese Foreign Minister last week, requesting clarification about the situation of those detained.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-01-12T16:36:45.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444010/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444010/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","China: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the recent arrests of lawyers and opposition activists in China.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","902983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444011","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>I led a trade delegation of 40 companies to Morocco in November, reconfirming our close bilateral relationship and demonstrating the potential to expand our trade links.</p><p>I have no firm plans to return at present, but am pleased that the Moroccan Ministers of Energy and Justice are visiting the UK later this month.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-12T16:24:38.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444011/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444011/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Morocco: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he next plans to visit the Kingdom of Morocco.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","902973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444012","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-12","<p>We welcome the signature of the Libyan Political Agreement on 17 December which paves the way for a new Government of National Accord in Libya. The security situation remains fragile and it is vital that the new government is formed quickly to tackle the threats from Daesh and people smuggling.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-12T16:26:24.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444012/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444012/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-06","Libya: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the security and political situation in Libya.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","902977"
